    "index_reference": "gershom",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<h1>GERSHOM</h1><ol><li><p>Moses’s son by Zipporah, born in Midian when Moses was forced to flee from Egypt (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:22\">Exodus 2:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod18:3\">18:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:15-1Chr23:16\">1&nbsp;Chronicles 23:15–16</a>).</p></li><li><p>Jonathan’s father. He and his sons served as priests for the tribe of Dan. The people of Dan made a carved statue to worship as a god, breaking God&apos;s command against idols. They chose Jonathan, Gershom&apos;s son, to be their priest and lead their worship (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg18:30\">Judges 18:30</a>).</p></li><li><p>An alternate spelling of Gershon, Levi’s oldest son (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr6:1,1Chr6:16-1Chr6:17,1Chr6:20,1Chr6:43\">1&nbsp;Chronicles 6:1, 16–17, 20, 43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:6-1Chr23:7\">23:6–7</a>). </p><p><em>See</em> <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"4599\" data-resourceType=\"TyndaleBibleDictionary\">Gershon, Gershonites</span>.</p></li><li><p>An ancestor of Shebuel, the chief officer over the temple treasury during David’s reign (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr26:24\">1&nbsp;Chronicles 26:24</a>).</p></li><li><p>Phinehas’s son who returned with Ezra after the exile in Babylon (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra8:2\">Ezra 8:2</a>).</p></li></ol>",
